title: Static Analysis

android.permission.ACCESS_COARSE_LOCATIO.description: Access coarse location sources, such as the mobile network database, to determine an approximate phone location, where available. Malicious applications can use this to determine approximately where you are.

android.permission.ACCESS_FINE_LOCATION.description: Access fine location sources, such as the Global Positioning System on the phone, where available. Malicious applications can use this to determine where you are and may consume additional battery power.

android.permission.ACCESS_NETWORK_STATE.description: Allows an application to view the status of all networks.

android.permission.INTERNET.description: Allows an application to create network sockets.

android.permission.VIBRATE.description: Allows the application to control the vibrator.

android.permission.WAKE_LOCK.description: Allows an application to prevent the phone from going to sleep.

android.permission.FOREGROUND_SERVICE.info: enables regular apps to use Service.startForeground.
android.permission.FOREGROUND_SERVICE.description: Allows a regular application to use Service.startForeground.

android.permission.FOREGROUND_SERVICE_LO.info: allows foreground services with location use.
android.permission.FOREGROUND_SERVICE_LO.description: Allows a regular application to use Service.startForeground with the type "location".

com.google.android.c2dm.permission.RECEI.description: Allows an application to receive push notifications from cloud.

com.google.android.gms.permission.AD_ID.description: This app uses a Google advertising ID and can possibly serve advertisements.

android.permission.RECEIVE_BOOT_COMPLETE.description: Allows an application to start itself as soon as the system has finished booting. This can make it take longer to start the phone and allow the application to slow down the overall phone by always running.

android.permission.POST_NOTIFICATIONS.info: allows an app to post notifications.
android.permission.POST_NOTIFICATIONS.description: Allows an app to post notifications

android.permission.ACCESS_BACKGROUND_LOC.description: Allows an app to access location in the background.

android.permission.ACCESS_NOTIFICATION_P.info: marker permission for accessing notification policy.
android.permission.ACCESS_NOTIFICATION_P.description: Marker permission for applications that wish to access notification policy.

android.permission.READ_PHONE_STATE.description: Allows the application to access the phone features of the device. An application with this permission can determine the phone number and serial number of this phone, whether a call is active, the number that call is connected to and so on.

android.permission.ACCESS_ADSERVICES_ATT.info: allow applications to access advertising service attribution
android.permission.ACCESS_ADSERVICES_ATT.description: This enables the app to retrieve information related to advertising attribution, which can be used for targeted advertising purposes. App can gather data about how users interact with ads, such as clicks or impressions, to measure the effectiveness of advertising campaigns.

android.permission.ACCESS_ADSERVICES_AD_.info: allow app to access the device's advertising ID.
android.permission.ACCESS_ADSERVICES_AD_.description: This ID is a unique, user-resettable identifier provided by Google's advertising services, allowing apps to track user behavior for advertising purposes while maintaining user privacy.

com.google.android.finsky.permission.BIN.description: A custom permission defined by Google.

Broadcast Receiver (com.google.android.gms.gcm.GcmReceiver) is Protected by a permission, but the protection level of the permission should be checked.
Permission: com.google.android.c2dm.permission.SEND
[android:exported=true]
manifest_findings.description: A Broadcast Receiver is found to be shared with other apps on the device therefore leaving it accessible to any other application on the device. It is protected by a permission which is not defined in the analysed application. As a result, the protection level of the permission should be checked where it is defined. If it is set to normal or dangerous, a malicious application can request and obtain the permission and interact with the component. If it is set to signature, only applications signed with the same certificate can obtain the permission.

"Respond.CPR.LearnMore.Answer10" : "Les chances pour le coeur de recommencer à battre seulement grâce aux compressions de poitrine sont minimes. Pour faire en sorte que le coeur recommence à battre il faut avoir recours généralement au choc électrique d'un défibrillateur. Les pressions de poitrine ne vont que pomper légèrement le sang afin d'essayer de conserver les organes en vie, tout spécialement le cerveau. Il est probable que vous ne voyiez pas de changements visibles dans l´état de la personne que vous essayez de resussciter mais il ne faut pas abandonner car les compressions de poitrine augmentent de façon significative les possibilités de survie des personnes resusscités lorsque les urgences surviennent."

"Respond.CPR.LearnMore.Answer8" : "If you feel able to, you can combine chest compressions with breathing into their mouth or nose. However, giving chest compressions is the most important because their blood already has some oxygen in it and the compressions will keep that blood pumping about their body, taking oxygen to their brain. Breathing into their mouth or nose adds oxygen in their lungs. The combination of continuous cycles of 30 chest compressions followed by two breaths is called CPR (cardiopulmonary resuscitation)."

"Respond.CPR.LearnMore.Answer8" : "Si se siente capaz, puede combinar las compresiones torácicas con la técnica de respiración boca a boca. Sin embargo las compresiones torácicas son lo mas importante porque su sangre ya tiene algo de oxígeno y las compresiones bombearán la sangre por el cuerpo, llevando oxígeno al cerebro. La combinación de ciclos continuos de 30 compresiones torácicas seguidas por dos exhalaciones se denomina RCP (Resucitación Cardio Pulmonar)."

"Respond.CPR.LearnMore.Answer10" : "胸部圧迫のみで心肺蘇生させる可能性は極めて低く、通常は除細動器を使用して心臓に電気ショックを与える必要がある。胸骨圧迫により少量の血液を体内に循環させ、内臓器官を存続させることができる。とりわけ、脳を維持することが重要である。傷病者の状態に目立った変化が見られなくとも諦めてはならない。胸骨圧迫をすることで、救急隊が到着した時に傷病者が蘇生する可能性は著しく高くなる。"

"Respond.CPR.LearnMore.Answer8" : "もし可能であれば、胸骨圧迫と（口、または鼻への）人工呼吸を併せて行ってください。しかし、血液中にはすでに酸素が含まれており、圧迫することにより血液の循環を促し、脳に酸素を届ける役目を果たすため、胸骨圧迫をすることが最も重要とされています。胸骨圧迫を継続して30回行った後、人工呼吸を2回することをCPR（心肺蘇生法）と言います。"

"Respond.CPR.LearnMore.Answer10" : "The chance of restarting the heart by chest compressions alone is very low. To restart, a heart usually needs an electric shock from a defibrillator. Chest compressions pump a small amount of blood around the body to keep the organs – most importantly the brain – alive. You may not see any visible change in the person’s condition, but don’t give up. Chest compressions significantly increase the possibility of the person being successfully resuscitated when the emergency services turn up."

"Respond.CPR.LearnMore.Answer10" : "La probabilidad de reactivar el corazón mediante compresiones torácicas es muy baja. Para reactivarse, un corazón normalmente necesita la descarga eléctrica de un desfibrilador. Las compresiones torácicas bombean una pequeña cantidad de sangre por el cuerpo para mantener los órganos -y sobre todo el cerebro- vivos. Puede que no vea ningún cambio en la condición de la persona, pero no deje de hacerlo. Las compresiones torácicas incrementan significativamente las posibilidades de que la persona sea resucitada con éxito cuando lleguen los servicios de emergencia."

"Respond.CPR.LearnMore.Answer8" : "Si vous en êtes capable, vous pouvez combiner les compressions sur la poitrine avec des expirations dans la bouge ou dans le nez. Avec le simple fait de faire les compressions sur la poitrine, c'est la chose la plus importante à faire à ce moment car le sang de la personne contient déjà de l'oxygène et les compressions vont alors permettre que le sang circule aussi moindrement au travers du corps, en ramenant l'oxygène au cerveau. Avec les expirations dans la bouche ou le nez de la personne inconsciente vous aussi faire parvenir de l'oxygène dans les poumons de la personne. La combinaison de plusieurs cycles de 30 compressions suivies de deux expirations s'appelle RCP (réanimation cardio-pulmonaire)."

playstore_details.title: PulsePoint Respond
playstore_details.description:
PulsePoint Respond is a 911-connected app that can immediately inform you of emergencies occurring in your community and can request your help when CPR is needed nearby.

PulsePoint helps create an informed and engaged community that drives a “Culture of Action,” a key strategy in strengthening the Chain of Survival for cardiac arrest victims. In addition to nearby “CPR-needed” notifications, you can choose to be notified of significant events that may impact you and your family. These informational notifications provide an early heads-up to local threats such as wildland fires, flooding and utility emergencies. You can even monitor live dispatch radio traffic for most PulsePoint-connected communities with a simple tap on the speaker icon.

PulsePoint currently provides coverage for thousands of cities and communities, with many more on the way. For more information, visit pulsepoint.org, contact us at info@pulsepoint.org, or join the conversation at Facebook and Twitter.

PulsePoint not yet available in your community? Although we are working hard to make public safety agencies aware of PulsePoint, you can help by expressing interest to your local fire chief, EMS official, and elected officials such as your mayor, council member or supervisor. A simple note, phone call or public meeting comment would ensure that they are aware of PulsePoint. We have found that City Hall does listen and is quite willing to bring PulsePoint to the community.

PulsePoint is a 501(c)(3) public non-profit foundation.
playstore_details.summary: Download the PulsePoint app and use your CPR skills to save a life!

hotspot.title: Found 5 critical permission(s)
hotspot.description:
Ensure that these permissions are required by the application.

android.permission.ACCESS_COARSE_LOCATION (dangerous): coarse (network-based) location - Access coarse location sources, such as the mobile network database, to determine an approximate phone location, where available. Malicious applications can use this to determine approximately where you are.

android.permission.ACCESS_FINE_LOCATION (dangerous): fine (GPS) location - Access fine location sources, such as the Global Positioning System on the phone, where available. Malicious applications can use this to determine where you are and may consume additional battery power.

android.permission.POST_NOTIFICATIONS (dangerous): allows an app to post notifications. - Allows an app to post notifications

android.permission.ACCESS_BACKGROUND_LOCATION (dangerous): access location in background - Allows an app to access location in the background.

android.permission.READ_PHONE_STATE (dangerous): read phone state and identity - Allows the application to access the phone features of the device. An application with this permission can determine the phone number and serial number of this phone, whether a call is active, the number that call is connected to and so on.
